title: Must-see: 'Price is Right' model takes a tumble, smashes set...
text:
Come on down!
Amber Lancaster, a model on the popular game show "The Price Is Right," is making headlines after she took a tumble on Friday's show, smashing a set light in the process.
Lancaster was cheering on contestant Leah, who was screaming and jumping with glee after guessing the price of an ATV in Double Prices.
>> Read more trending stories
After Lancaster stumbled in her heels and shattered the glass light bulb, Leah gasped. "Did I do that?" the contestant asked.
Later, Leah turned to Lancaster and asked, "Are you OK?" Lancaster's response: "Yeah, I'm fine. I'm just gonna die of embarrassment."
Lancaster even tweeted about the incident.
